quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to calculate the sum of myArray's elements using the for loop, and print to the screen. myArray is an array of doubles containing 4 elements.
[!raw!]
double sum = 0.0;
for (int x = 0; x < {0}; x++) {
  sum += myArray[x];
}
{1} << sum << endl;

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Arrays in Calculations[/h1]

The following code creates a program that uses a [b]for [/b]loop to calculate the sum of all elements of an array.[code format="cpp" codeId="220"]int arr[] = {11, 35, 62, 555, 989};
int sum = 0; 

for (int x = 0; x < 5; x++) {
  sum += arr[x];
}

cout << sum << endl;
//Outputs 1652[/code]
To review, we declared an array and a variable [b]sum [/b]that will hold the sum of the elements.
Next, we utilized a [b]for [/b]loop to iterate through each element of the array, and added the corresponding element's value to our [b]sum [/b]variable. 
[note]In the array, the first element's index is 0, so the [b]for [/b]loop initializes the [b]x[/b] variable to 0.[/note]
